ZH: 他在战场上受苦了很久。
EN: He suffered a lot on the battlefield.

ZH: 她在失恋后受苦很久。
EN: She suffered for a long time after the breakup.

ZH: 孩子们受苦于缺乏水和食物。
EN: The children suffered from lack of water and food.

ZH: 这项任务会让你受苦一段时间。
EN: This task will make you suffer for a while.

ZH: 他们因为寒冷天气而受苦。
EN: They suffered because of the cold weather.

ZH: 种族受苦于不公正对待。
EN: The minority suffered from unfair treatment.

ZH: 那个地区的居民经历了数年的受苦。
EN: The residents of that area experienced years of suffering.

ZH: 战争给人民带来了很多不必要的受苦。
EN: War brought a lot of unnecessary suffering to the people.

ZH: 她愿意受苦为了保护自己的家人。
EN: She was willing to suffer to protect her family.

ZH: 当他们意识到真相时，感到非常受苦。
EN: They felt very suffering when they realized the truth.

ZH: 饥饿的人们每天都在受苦。
EN: Hungry people suffer every day.

ZH: 失去亲人是一种特别痛苦的受苦。
EN: Losing loved ones is a particularly painful suffering.

ZH: 呼吸困难让他感到受苦不堪。
EN: Difficulty in breathing made him suffer unbearable.

ZH: 滥用药物会给身体带来很多受苦。
EN: Drug abuse can cause a lot of suffering to the body.

ZH: 作为父母，我们不愿看到孩子受苦。
EN: As parents, we do not want to see our children suffer.

ZH: 那个国家的人民长期以来一直在受苦受难。
EN: The people of that country have long been suffering.

ZH: 在失败中学到的教训让他感到受苦。
EN: The lessons learned from failure made him suffer.

ZH: 他生病在床上受苦了很长时间。
EN: He has been suffering in bed for a long time.

ZH: 贫困使人们受苦于缺乏基本生活条件。
EN: Poverty makes people suffer from lack of basic living conditions. 

ZH: 为了信仰，他们宁愿受苦也不改变初衷。
EN: For their faith, they would rather suffer than change their minds.
